    <note>Li(2) Zhaoshu [987] Fang(3)'s [8075] grandson, Zhaogou's [986] brother, Zhaomai's [7275] cousin, Shangqing's [7040] father, Cao(1) Bin's [8134] grandson-in-law, father of Zhang(2) Dexiang's [344] son-in-law. Zhaoshu's son-in-law Ren(1) Gongzhi's [3428] father was Ren(1) Zhongshi [877]. Their generational names indicate that Li(2) Gaoqing [1049] was a nephew and Shijing [1077], Shiguan [1081] and that Shiliang [1082] were grandsons or grandnephews. Wang(2) Yuan(2)'s [7385] son-in-law, Li(2) Shimou [3527], has the same generational name as his grandsons and grandnephews. Zhaoshu was appointed Qunmu panguan on the basis of the recommendation of the Qunmu zhizhi shi, Cao(1) Liyong [8133]. XCB, 113.2a, 127.3a; Hu Su, WJ, 38.6a-12b; SS, 265.9a-9b; YLDD, 12399.7a, 16a. CBD, 2, 1006-7.</note>
